Here is a very cool Squier "Custom Shack Strat" Gilmore style. The Squier maple neck has near zero fret wear ,and has had a nice headstock make over with many coats of cleat over the decal. The previous owner had put different tuners on at one time but now the tuners are back to the original Squier tuners. You can see where I filled the holes left over on the back of the headstock. The very cool Gloss Black Body looks very nice,has a few tiny pin head size chips to the finish,otherwise mild surface scratches. The pickups has been upgraded with SEM single coil pickups. The guitar has been wired for tone control on all three pickups.The bridge and neck pickups both work with the neck pickups tone control. Nice to have tone control on the bridge pickup,makes it a lot more versatile. All electronics work perfectly,and sound great on every setting,clean or with some distortion. The capacitor has been upgraded with a .022 Orange Drop style epoxy film capacitor . More range of tone control and a smoother response. Action is good and guitar plays very nicely. This guitar sounds really good,and it looks like a classic. This "Custom Shack" came out great!!! A very sexy looking guitar,great colors.
